07, who grew deeply attached to her. Upon his 1873 death his estate provided her an annuity and a funeral fund — recognition outside any acknowledged Burr legacy."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Wrote father Burr for Theodosia's portrait miniature","body":"Letters from Louisa to her unacknowledged father Aaron Burr survived among his papers. In one she asked him to lend a miniature portrait of his 'beloved Theodosia' — half-sister Theodosia Burr Alston, lost at sea in 1813 — so that brother John Pierre Burr could copy it. The three unacknowledged Burr children — Louisa, John Pierre, and the recognized Theodosia — had a documented sibling relationship across the color line that Burr never publicly acknowledged."}],"slug":"louisa-darius-1788"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}